A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring and celebrating the 80th birthday of Marilyn Arrington; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, born on March 4, 1945, in Rome, Georgia, Marilyn Arrington has dedicated her
3 life to education, service, and community advocacy; and
4 WHEREAS, she is a proud graduate of Clark College, Class of 1966, and furthered her
5 education by obtaining both a master's and a specialist's degree from Georgia State
6 University, demonstrating an unwavering commitment to lifelong learning, including her
7 enrollment in a doctoral program at Georgia State University in 2021; and
8 WHEREAS, Marilyn Arrington dedicated over 30 years to shaping young minds in the
9 Atlanta Public Schools system, beginning her career at the historic Booker T. Washington
10 High School and later extending her impact by teaching GED preparation at Atlanta
11 Technical College, helping countless students achieve their educational goals; and
12 WHEREAS, she has exemplified a spirit of service and leadership for over 50 years as a
13 Golden Member of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated, and as a charter member of
14 the Pi Alpha Omega Chapter, established in 1985; and
