15 WHEREAS, she has also been a distinguished alumnae member of The Links, Incorporated,
16 Azalea City Chapter, and an active member of the Clark Atlanta University Guild, further
17 strengthening her commitment to education, mentorship, and community enrichment; and
18 WHEREAS, as a devoted and longtime member of Cascade United Methodist Church for
19 over 40 years, she has served on the Executive Board, providing leadership and guidance to
20 her faith community; and
21 WHEREAS, Marilyn Arrington is a proud resident of Southwest Atlanta, where she has lived
22 on Cascade Road for 44 years, making a lasting impact as a community servant, advocate,
23 and engaged neighbor; and
24 WHEREAS, she is known for her love of the arts and entertainment, her adventurous spirit
25 as a member of the Nature Gurlz, and her deep commitment to family as a mother,
26 grandmother, aunt, niece, sister, and friend; and
27 WHEREAS, as she celebrates this milestone 80th birthday, it is fitting and proper to
28 recognize her extraordinary contributions, enduring legacy, and the countless lives she has
29 touched throughout her journey.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
31 honor and celebrate the remarkable life of Marilyn Arrington, extend heartfelt
32 congratulations on her 80th birthday, and express profound gratitude for her decades of
33 service, leadership, and unwavering dedication to education and community empowerment.
34 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
35 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Marilyn Arrington.
